<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1755">
Given a string, your task is to reorder its letters in such a way that it becomes a palindrome (i.e., it reads the same forwards and backwards).<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has a string of length $n$ consisting of characters Aâ€“Z.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print a palindrome consisting of the characters of the original string. You may print any valid solution. If there are no solutions, print &quot;NO SOLUTION&quot;.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 10^6$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>AAAACACBA</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>AACABACAA</code>    </div>
